.TH FASTERFETCH 1 "2026" "fasterfetch" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
fasterfetch \- a retro distro information fetcher
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B fasterfetch
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B fasterfetch
displays system information alongside ASCII art, centered in the terminal.
It reads system data directly from kernel interfaces — no shell subprocesses.
Works on Linux and macOS.
.PP
Displayed fields: OS, Kernel, Uptime, Shell, Terminal, CPU (with temperature),
GPU, Packages, Memory, Disk, Battery, and Local IP (when present).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-ascii " " \fIfile\fR
Load ASCII art from \fIfile\fR instead of the default.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force\-logo " " \fIname\fR
Force a built-in distro logo. Supported names:
.BR arch ", " debian ", " ubuntu ", " fedora ", " alpine ", " kali ", " gentoo ", "
.BR mint ", " nixos ", " redhat ", " linux ", " macos ", " default .
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-theme " " \fIname\fR
Apply a named color theme to borders and labels.
Available themes:
.BR nord ", " dracula ", " gruvbox ", " catppuccin ", " amber ", " default .
.br
\fBdefault\fR auto-selects a color based on the running distro.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-no\-center\-v
Disable full-screen vertical centering. Useful for scrollback-friendly output.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage summary and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/fasterfetch/ascii.txt
User-specific ASCII art. Checked first (after \fB\-a\fR).
.TP
.I /usr/share/fasterfetch/ascii.txt
System-wide default ASCII art installed by \fBmake install\fR.
.TP
.I ./ascii.txt
Fallback when running from the source directory.
.SH EXAMPLES
Run with default settings:
.PP
.RS
.B fasterfetch
.RE
.PP
Use the Nord color theme without vertical centering:
.PP
.RS
.B fasterfetch \-t nord \-n
.RE
.PP
Force the macOS Apple logo with Dracula colors:
.PP
.RS
.B fasterfetch \-f macos \-t dracula
.RE
.PP
Use a custom ASCII art file:
.PP
.RS
.B fasterfetch \-a ~/my-art.txt
.RE
